<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17684] Issue in SolrJ Reference Guide (Ping) - Incorrect Status Retrieval</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17684</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SolrJ Reference Guide provides incorrect examples for retrieving the ping status of a collection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/guide/solr/9_8/deployment-guide/ping.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.apache.org/guide/solr/9_8/deployment-guide/ping.html&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Issues:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pingResponse.getStatus() returns the status of the ping request itself (status=0), not the collection&apos;s ping status (&quot;OK&quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Since getResponse() returns a NamedList&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt;, the value must be explicitly cast to a String or converted using .toString().&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Correction:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The correct way to retrieve the collection&apos;s ping status:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; status = (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;) process.getResponse().get(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;status&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);  
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; status = process.getResponse().get(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;status&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).toString();  
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
